{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T06:54:55.516Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Xavier/Glorot initialization"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a weight initialization technique that keeps the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "variance of activations constant across all layers"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", preventing vanishing and exploding gradients during training. It's one of the most widely used methods for initializing weight matrices in neural networks."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Xavier/Glorot — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Xavier/Glorot Initialization Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Developed by "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Xavier Glorot"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (and colleagues) in 2010, this method initializes weights from a distribution with "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "zero mean"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "variance scaled by the number of input and output connections"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Name"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": \"Xavier\" (from author's name) = \"Glorot\" (from paper title author)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Purpose"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Maintain stable signal propagation through deep networks"}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why It Matters: The Problem It Solves"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Bad Initialization Problems"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Initialization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Problem"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Result"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "All zeros"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Every neuron learns the same thing (symmetry)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Network can't learn"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Too large"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Activations explode → saturate"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Exploding gradients"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Too small"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Activations vanish → near zero"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Vanishing gradients"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Xavier solves this"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": By keeping activation variance constant across layers, gradients flow smoothly backward without vanishing or exploding."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How Xavier Works: The Math"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Core Idea"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Initialize weights such that:\n\\[\n\\text{Var}(a^{[l]}) = \\text{Var}(a^{[l-1]}) \\quad \\text{(constant variance across layers)}\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Derivation Assumptions"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Weights and inputs are "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "centered at zero"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (mean = 0)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Weights and inputs are "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "independent and identically distributed"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (IID)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Biases initialized as "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "zeros"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Using "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "tanh"}, {"type": "text", "text": " activation (approximately linear for small inputs)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Xavier Formulas"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For a layer with:\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "n_{\\text{in}}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = number of input neurons (fan-in)\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "n_{\\text{out}}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = number of output neurons (fan-out)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Glorot Uniform"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n\\[\nW \\sim \\mathcal{U}\\left(-\\sqrt{\\frac{6}{n"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{\\text{in}} + n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\\text{out}}}}, \\ \\sqrt{\\frac{6}{n"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{\\text{in}} + n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\\text{out}}}}\\right)\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Glorot Normal"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n\\[\nW \\sim \\mathcal{N}\\left(0, \\ \\sqrt{\\frac{2}{n"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{\\text{in}} + n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\\text{out}}}}\\right)\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key insight"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Variance = "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\frac{2}{n_{\\text{in}} + n_{\\text{out}}}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " — the average of fan-in and fan-out."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why the Formula Works"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For a linear layer: "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "z = Wx"}}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "If inputs have variance "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\text{Var}(x)"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " and weights have variance "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\text{Var}(W)"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n\\[\n\\text{Var}(z) = n"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{\\text{in}} \\cdot \\text{Var}(W) \\cdot \\text{Var}(x)\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "To keep "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\text{Var}(z) = \\text{Var}(x)"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ", we need:\n\\[\n\\text{Var}(W) = \\frac{1}{n"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{\\text{in}}}\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "But Xavier also considers "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "backpropagation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (gradients flowing backward), which depends on "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "n_{\\text{out}}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ". The compromise is:\n\\[\n\\text{Var}(W) = \\frac{2}{n"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{\\text{in}} + n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\\text{out}}}\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "This balances forward signal propagation and backward gradient flow."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to Use Xavier/Glorot"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Component"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Recommendation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Activation function"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Sigmoid"}, {"type": "text", "text": " or "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "tanh"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (zero-mean activations)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Layer type"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Fully connected"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (dense) layers"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Not for"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "ReLU"}, {"type": "text", "text": " activations (use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "He initialization"}, {"type": "text", "text": " instead)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Why not ReLU?"}, {"type": "text", "text": " ReLU kills half the inputs (negative values → 0), so we need higher variance to compensate → He initialization uses "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\sqrt{\\frac{2}{n_{\\text{in}}}}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " instead."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Practical Implementation"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "TensorFlow/Keras"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import tensorflow.keras.initializers as init\n\n# Glorot Uniform (default for dense layers in TF)\ninitializer = init.GlorotUniform()\n\n# Glorot Normal\ninitializer = init.GlorotNormal()\n\n# Use in layer\nmodel.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, kernel_initializer=initializer, activation='tanh'))"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "PyTorch"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch.nn.init as init\n\n# Xavier Uniform\ninit.xavier_uniform_(layer.weight)\n\n# Xavier Normal  \ninit.xavier_normal_(layer.weight)\n\n# With gain parameter for different activations\ninit.xavier_normal_(layer.weight, gain=1.0)  # tanh: gain≈1.716, sigmoid: gain≈1.0"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Manual Implementation"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\ndef xavier_init(n_in, n_out, scale=1.0):\n    variance = scale * 2.0 / (n_in + n_out)\n    return np.random.randn(n_in, n_out) * np.sqrt(variance)\n\n# Example: layer with 784 inputs, 128 outputs\nW = xavier_init(784, 128)"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Xavier vs. Other Initialization Methods"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Method"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Formula"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best for"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Variance"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Xavier/Glorot"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\sqrt{\\frac{2}{n_{\\text{in}} + n_{\\text{out}}}}"}}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sigmoid, tanh"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\frac{2}{n_{\\text{in}} + n_{\\text{out}}}"}}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "He (Kaiming)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\sqrt{\\frac{2}{n_{\\text{in}}}}"}}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "ReLU, Leaky ReLU"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\frac{2}{n_{\\text{in}}}"}}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Zero"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "0"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Biases only"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "0 (bad for weights)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Random small"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\mathcal{N}(0, 0.01)"}}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Legacy, simple nets"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Constant (not scaled)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key difference"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Xavier uses "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "average of fan-in and fan-out"}, {"type": "text", "text": "; He uses "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "only fan-in"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (because ReLU breaks symmetry)."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mental Model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Think of Xavier initialization as "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "\"volume control\""}, {"type": "text", "text": " for your neural network:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Too loud"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (large weights): Signals explode → saturate → can't learn"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Too quiet"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (small weights): Signals vanish → disappear → can't learn"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Xavier"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Perfect volume → signals flow steadily through all layers"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Each layer passes the signal forward at the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "same strength"}, {"type": "text", "text": " it received, so deep networks don't amplify or suppress the signal."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Xavier/Glorot"}, {"type": "text", "text": " initializes weights to keep "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "activation variance constant"}, {"type": "text", "text": " across layers"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formulas"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Uniform "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\mathcal{U}(-\\sqrt{\\frac{6}{n_{\\text{in}}+n_{\\text{out}}}}, \\sqrt{\\dots})"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " or Normal "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\mathcal{N}(0, \\sqrt{\\frac{2}{n_{\\text{in}}+n_{\\text{out}}}})"}}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Best for"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Sigmoid/tanh"}, {"type": "text", "text": " activations and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "fully connected"}, {"type": "text", "text": " layers"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Not for"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "ReLU"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "He initialization"}, {"type": "text", "text": ")"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Why it works"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Balances forward signal propagation (depends on "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "n_{\\text{in}}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ") and backward gradient flow (depends on "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "n_{\\text{out}}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ")"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Prevents "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "vanishing/exploding gradients"}, {"type": "text", "text": " → enables stable training of deep networks"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Default in many frameworks (TensorFlow's "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "Dense"}, {"type": "text", "text": " layer uses GlorotUniform by default)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Proper initialization like Xavier is the \"secret sauce\" for fast convergence and stable training—you're essentially planting seeds in fertile soil instead of dead concrete."}]}]}}